Sentencas: A composite of NiO-BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-delta (NiO-BZCY) was successfully prepared by a simple one-step-combustion process and applied as an anode for solid oxide fuel cells based on stable La2Ce2O7 (LCO) electrolyte.
Titulo: New ionic diffusion strategy to fabricate proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells based on a stable La2Ce2O7 electrolyte

Sentencas: A high open circuit voltage of 1.00 V and a maximum power density of 315 mW cm(-2) were obtained with NiO-BZCY anode and LCO electrolyte when measured at 700 degrees C using humidified hydrogen fuel.
Titulo: New ionic diffusion strategy to fabricate proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells based on a stable La2Ce2O7 electrolyte

Sentencas: SEM-EDX and Raman results suggested that a thin BaCeO3-based reaction layer about 5 mu m in thickness was formed at the anode/electrolyte interface for Ba cations partially migrated from anode into the electrolyte film.
Titulo: New ionic diffusion strategy to fabricate proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells based on a stable La2Ce2O7 electrolyte

Sentencas: Impedance spectra analysis showed that the activation energy for LCO conductivity differed with the anode materials, about 52.51 kJ mol(-1) with NiO-BZCY anode and 95.08 kJ mol(-1) with NiO-LCO anode.
Titulo: New ionic diffusion strategy to fabricate proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells based on a stable La2Ce2O7 electrolyte

Sentencas: The great difference in these activation energies might suggest that the formed BaCeO3 reaction layer could promote the proton transferring numbers of LCO electrolyte.
Titulo: New ionic diffusion strategy to fabricate proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells based on a stable La2Ce2O7 electrolyte
